         <div type="translation" source="bib:Hultzsch1900-1901_06">
 	<!--translation encoded as per EGD §9.2 -->
<div type="textpart" n="A"><head xml:lang="eng">Seal</head>
<p n="1">(The seal) of the Mahārāja, the glorious Jayavarman, who belongs to the <foreign>gotra</foreign> of the Br̥hatphalāyanas.</p>
</div>
<div type="textpart" n="B"><head xml:lang="eng">Plates</head>
<p>(First plate, first side.) (Order referring) to the <foreign>brahmadeya</foreign> Pāṇṭūra in Kūdūrāhāra,
(granted) to 8 people, to Brāhmaṇas, to the <foreign>mahājana</foreign>s (headed by) Savagutaja.<!-- n8 --></p>
<p n="1-6">(From the camp of victory, the town Kūdūraa, — the fortunate<!-- n3 --> king, the glorious
Jayavarman, who is favoured by the feet of Maheśvara (and) who belongs to the <foreign>gotra</foreign> of the
Br̥hatphalāyanas, orders (his) official (<foreign>vyāpr̥ta</foreign>) at Kūdūraa (as follows): —</p>
<p n="7-24">“For conferring on ourselves victory (in war) and for increasing (our) length of life,
we have now given the village Pāṇṭūra in the district of Kūdūraa (<foreign>Kūdūrāhāra</foreign>) (as) a
<foreign>brahmadeya</foreign>, assigning 24 shares<!-- n4 --> to 8 people, (<foreign>viz.</foreign>) to (the following) Brāhmaṇas:
<list>
<item>to Savagutaja (Śarvaguptārya), a householder<!-- n5 --> of the Gautama gotra, 8 (shares);</item>
<item>to Sagivija of the Tānavya (<foreign>gotra</foreign>) 3 shares;</item>
<item>to Goginaja 3 shares;</item> 
<item>to Bhavannaja of the Kauṇḍinya <foreign>gotra</foreign> two — 2 — shares;</item>
<item>to Rudavennhuja (Rudraviṣṇvārya) of the Bhāradvāja (<foreign>gotra</foreign>) one and a half share;</item> 
<item>to Īsaradataja (Īśvaradattārya) of the Kārṣṇāyana (<foreign>gotra</foreign>) one and a half share;</item> 
<item>to Rudaghosaja {Rudraghoṣārya) of the Aupamanyava (<foreign>gotra</foreign>) 1 share;</item> 
<item>and to Khandarudaja (Skandarudrārya) of the Kauśika <foreign>gotra</foreign> half a share.</item>
</list></p>
<p n="25-27">“Parcel off<!-- n1 --> that village Pāṇṭūra from this (district), having made (it) a
<foreign>brahmadeya</foreign>.</p>
<p n="28-30">“And to this village Pāṇṭūra we grant (all) immunities, having made (it) a <foreign>brahmadeya</foreign>.</p>
<p n="31-34">“(Let it be) free from being entered, free from being meddled with, free from diggings for salt, <foreign>araṭhasaṁvinayika</foreign>, and endowed with immunities of all kinds.</p>
<p n="35">“Exempt<!-- n2 --> (it) with (all) these immunities.</p>
<p n="36-37">“And having made this village Pāṇṭūra a <foreign>brahmadeya</foreign>, cause a charter to be
drawn ups to this effect.”</p>
<p n="38">The order was issued by word of mouth.<!-- n4 --></p>
<p n="39">(The charter) was signed<!-- n5 --> by (the king) himself. Fortune, wealth, power<!-- n6 --> and
victory<!-- n7 --> were given (by the donees to the king as a reward for the grant).</p>
<p n="40">(This) set of plates was prepared on the 1st day of the 1st fortnight of winter of the 10th year by the Mahādaṇḍanāyaka Bhāpahānavarman, the best of the Mahātagi (family?).</p>
</div>
